Mary Wickes https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mary_Wickes 0 Mary Wickes (born Mary Isabella Wickenhauser, June 13, 1910 – October 22, 1995) was an American film and television character actress. She often played supporting roles as prim, professional women, secretaries, nurses, and housekeepers, who made sarcastic quips when the leading characters fell short of her high standards.
